# Blog post writing (eugenetheengineer.com)

When creating or editing a post in `_posts/`, complete **all** applicable steps in the same change — before merge. Scheduled cron deploy will not add hub links for you.

## Slug

Derive from filename: `YYYY-MM-DD-<slug>.md` → `<slug>` (no date prefix).

Permalink: `/posts/<slug>/`

## Front matter (required)

- `title`, `date`, `description`, `tags`, `categories`, `author: eugene`
- `categories: [PostgreSQL Performance]` for PostgreSQL series pillars
- `redirect_from` with legacy `/YYYY/MM/DD/<slug>/` paths
- `render_with_liquid: false` unless the post body uses Liquid

## PostgreSQL Performance series

**Applies when** `categories` includes `PostgreSQL Performance`, or the post is a core chapter in the PG tuning series (indexing, EXPLAIN, query plans, RDS/Rails DB performance).

### 1. Content cluster (peer links on post page)

Add slug to `_data/content_clusters.yml` under `postgresql-performance`:

```yaml
postgresql-performance:
  - <slug>   # append; keep reading order if curated
```

Powers `_includes/cluster-links.html` (“More in this series”).

### 2. Playbook hub (auto on publish date)

Add slug to `_data/postgresql_playbook.yml` in **every** section that fits:

| Section | When |
|---------|------|
| `start_here` | Core reading-path chapter; add `blurb` (one sentence) |
| `foundational` | Only one anchor post (usually `sql-optimization-or-criminal-tracking`) |
| `problems` | Maps a symptom to the post; add `label`, `short_title`, optional `note` |
| `related` | PG-adjacent (billing indexes, Redis, ledger queries) — not core series |

Links render only after `date` passes (Jekyll + daily cron). No manual tab edits.

### 3. In-post links

- Link to [PostgreSQL Performance Playbook](/postgresql-performance-playbook/) at least once
- Cross-link 2–3 peers from `postgresql-performance` cluster

### 4. Verify

```bash
ruby tools/audit_playbook.rb
bundle exec jekyll build
```

## Other clusters

| Category | Cluster key in `_data/content_clusters.yml` |
|----------|-----------------------------------------------|
| Backend Engineering | `backend-engineering` |
| Billing & Fintech | `billing-fintech` |
| Architecture | `architecture` |
| Engineering Leadership | `engineering-leadership` |

Billing posts with heavy PostgreSQL index content may also belong in `postgresql_playbook.yml` → `problems` or `related` without joining `postgresql-performance` cluster.

## Do not

- Link to future-dated posts from published posts unless intentional preview
- Hand-edit `_tabs/postgresql-performance-playbook.md` for new series entries — use `_data/postgresql_playbook.yml`
